        "regulatory-limit reference, 'by-product ... below X ppm'.\n"
        "- Also No: declared not used in manufacturing, excluded by process, "
        "N/A. When genuinely ambiguous, default to No (conservative practice).\n\n"
        "STRICT CONSISTENCY (never violate):\n"
        "- present=Yes REQUIRES source in (vendor_coa, vendor_spec, usp_469) with "
        "a confirmed/per-batch RESULT.\n"
        "- present=Yes REQUIRES a non-null numeric limit string.\n"
        "- NEVER output Yes with limit=null or source=not_mentioned. If you cannot "
        "extract a numeric limit after scanning ALL pages, output Unknown.\n"
        "- Scan for numeric patterns: 'Not more than X ppm', 'NMT X ppm', "
        "'X PPM MAX', '≤ X ppm', '0.X%' (convert 0.5% = 5000 ppm).\n"
        "- Look inside sections titled 'Residual solvents', '12. Residual solvents' "
        "and numbered subsections, 'Impurities', 'Specifications', 'Tests'.\n\n"
        "DRL SAP MATERIAL CODE (strict priority):\n"
        "1. Label 'SAP CODE:' / 'SAP Code:' followed by a 6-9 digit number.\n"
        "2. Label 'Material Code:' followed by a number starting 10000/20000/"
        "30000/35000 (DRL SAP pattern).\n"
        "3. Label 'Product Code:' followed by a 6-9 digit DRL-style number.\n"
        "NEVER use as material_code: vendor internal codes (Ashland / CP Kelco / "
        "Roquette material numbers), batch/lot/order/delivery numbers, customer "
        "material numbers, GRN / A.R. / ATR numbers, specification numbers "
        "(SP-CFTO-… → drl_specification_no), or CAS numbers (→ cas_number). If no "
        "SAP CODE label is found, leave material_code EMPTY — never substitute. "
        "SAP codes may sit in a footer block or on page 2+.\n\n"
        "Return ONLY valid JSON (an OBJECT, never a bare array):\n"
        "{\n"
        '  "supplier_name": "",\n'
        '  "material_name": "",\n'
        '  "material_name_candidates": [],\n'
        '  "material_code": "",\n'
